The Evermeet underfoundation beneath the Kiess gate road has a persistent problem: shades from the buried city are accumulating in the lower passage system. The Antiquarian Society has documented three distinct manifestation points in the habitation quarter. These are not passive echoes — they impede access to significant archaeological material and have become aggressive toward researchers working the site. Clear three of the wandering shades from the lower passages so the research teams can work the area without constant disruption. The guild registrar has authorized compensation commensurate with the hazard.
The Kiess Antiquarian Society field team reports substantially reduced shade activity in the lower underfoundation passages. The manifestation points that were documented have gone quiet, and researchers have advanced their survey into previously blocked sections. The guild registrar has logged your contribution in the site research record, and the Society's archive notes the clearance as a meaningful contribution to continued access.
